10/06/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Romania's state minister in charge of defence, EU and justice issues, Ioan Talpes, arrived in Sofia on Wednesday (9 June). During a meeting with Bulgarian Deputy Prime Minister Plamen Panayotov, Talpes promised that Romania would do its best to close accession talks with the EU by late October or early November. The two countries would then be able to sign the EU accession treaty in May 2005 and join the Union on 1 January 2007. Talpes and Panayotov pledged the countries would co-operate and support each other to achieve their common goal. (Sega - 10/06/04; bTV, Mediapool - 09/06/04)
